comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-05T18:05:44.169Z",codex-release-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: ran pm search GitHub issue 21 npm install global git broken symlink ENOTEMPTY --limit 10. Results were closed install/history items,not an open tracker for GitHub issue #21,so this issue item records the external bug."
  "2026-05-05T18:50:27.864Z",codex-release-agent,"Documented registry-first global install/update path and added --repair install-script cleanup for stale git-source global installs. Evidence: release-readiness regression passed, full run-gates passed, clean npx and bunx published-package smoke checks passed from /tmp."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-05T18:05:44.169Z",codex-release-agent,"GitHub issue #21 reports npm install -g from the git repo can fail during reinstall and leave pm pointing to a deleted npm temp git clone. This is package-manager behavior,but the CLI release docs should make npm registry install/update the supported path and provide safe cleanup guidance for git-source installs."
